#: ../../../doc/en/development_guide.rst:3
msgid "Development Guide"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/development_guide.rst:5
msgid ""
"Some general guidelines regarding development in pytest for maintainers and "
"contributors. Nothing here is set in stone and can't be changed, feel free "
"to suggest improvements or changes in the workflow."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/development_guide.rst:10
msgid "Code Style"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/development_guide.rst:12
msgid "`PEP-8 <https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0008>`_"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/development_guide.rst:13
msgid "`flake8 <https://pypi.org/project/flake8/>`_ for quality checks"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/development_guide.rst:14
msgid "`invoke <http://www.pyinvoke.org/>`_ to automate development tasks"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/development_guide.rst:18
msgid "Branches"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/development_guide.rst:20
msgid "We have two long term branches:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/development_guide.rst:22
msgid "``master``: contains the code for the next bugfix release."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/development_guide.rst:23
msgid ""
"``features``: contains the code with new features for the next minor release."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/development_guide.rst:25
msgid ""
"The official repository usually does not contain topic branches, developers "
"and contributors should create topic branches in their own forks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/development_guide.rst:28
msgid ""
"Exceptions can be made for cases where more than one contributor is working "
"on the same topic or where it makes sense to use some automatic capability "
"of the main repository, such as automatic docs from `readthedocs "
"<readthedocs.org>`_ for a branch dealing with documentation refactoring."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/development_guide.rst:33
msgid "Issues"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/development_guide.rst:35
msgid ""
"Any question, feature, bug or proposal is welcome as an issue. Users are "
"encouraged to use them whenever they need."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/development_guide.rst:37
msgid ""
"GitHub issues should use labels to categorize them. Labels should be created "
"sporadically, to fill a niche; we should avoid creating labels just for the "
"sake of creating them."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/development_guide.rst:40
msgid ""
"Each label should include a description in the GitHub's interface stating "
"its purpose."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/development_guide.rst:42
msgid ""
"Labels are managed using `labels <https://github.com/hackebrot/labels>`_. "
"All the labels in the repository are kept in ``.github/labels.toml``, so any "
"changes should be via PRs to that file. After a PR is accepted and merged, "
"one of the maintainers must manually synchronize the labels file with the "
"GitHub repository."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/development_guide.rst:48
msgid "Temporary labels"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/development_guide.rst:50
msgid ""
"To classify issues for a special event it is encouraged to create a "
"temporary label. This helps those involved to find the relevant issues to "
"work on. Examples of that are sprints in Python events or global hacking "
"events."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/development_guide.rst:53
msgid ""
"``temporary: EP2017 sprint``: candidate issues or PRs tackled during the "
"EuroPython 2017"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/development_guide.rst:55
msgid ""
"Issues created at those events should have other relevant labels added as "
"well."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/development_guide.rst:57
msgid "Those labels should be removed after they are no longer relevant."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../HOWTORELEASE.rst:2
msgid "Release Procedure"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../HOWTORELEASE.rst:4
msgid ""
"Our current policy for releasing is to aim for a bugfix every few weeks and "
"a minor release every 2-3 months. The idea is to get fixes and new features "
"out instead of trying to cram a ton of features into a release and by "
"consequence taking a lot of time to make a new one."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../HOWTORELEASE.rst:10
msgid ""
"pytest releases must be prepared on **Linux** because the docs and examples "
"expect to be executed in that platform."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../HOWTORELEASE.rst:13
msgid "Create a branch ``release-X.Y.Z`` with the version for the release."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../HOWTORELEASE.rst:15
msgid "**patch releases**: from the latest ``master``;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../HOWTORELEASE.rst:17
msgid ""
"**minor releases**: from the latest ``features``; then merge with the latest "
"``master``;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../HOWTORELEASE.rst:19
msgid "Ensure your are in a clean work tree."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../HOWTORELEASE.rst:21
msgid "Using ``tox``, generate docs, changelog, announcements::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../HOWTORELEASE.rst:23
msgid "$ tox -e release -- <VERSION>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../HOWTORELEASE.rst:25
msgid "This will generate a commit with all the changes ready for pushing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../HOWTORELEASE.rst:27
msgid "Open a PR for this branch targeting ``master``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../HOWTORELEASE.rst:29
msgid ""
"After all tests pass and the PR has been approved, publish to PyPI by "
"pushing the tag::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../HOWTORELEASE.rst:31
msgid ""
"git tag <VERSION>\n"
"git push git@github.com:pytest-dev/pytest.git <VERSION>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../HOWTORELEASE.rst:34
msgid ""
"Wait for the deploy to complete, then make sure it is `available on PyPI "
"<https://pypi.org/project/pytest>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../HOWTORELEASE.rst:36
msgid "Merge the PR into ``master``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../HOWTORELEASE.rst:38
msgid "Send an email announcement with the contents from::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../HOWTORELEASE.rst:40
msgid "doc/en/announce/release-<VERSION>.rst"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../HOWTORELEASE.rst:42
msgid "To the following mailing lists:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../HOWTORELEASE.rst:44
msgid "pytest-dev@python.org (all releases)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../HOWTORELEASE.rst:45
msgid "python-announce-list@python.org (all releases)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../HOWTORELEASE.rst:46
msgid "testing-in-python@lists.idyll.org (only major/minor releases)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../HOWTORELEASE.rst:48
msgid ""
"And announce it on `Twitter <https://twitter.com/>`_ with the ``#pytest`` "
"hashtag."
msgstr ""
